Author: fishysandwich
Text: you need to go see someone before it's too late.  even if you think you're not "sick enough," because the part of your brain that is disordered is going to try and convince you that you're fine, just drop a couple pounds first, etc.  because that was me 4 years ago, and I'm still struggling with my eating disorder everyday, whether I'm feeling good mentally or not.

Author: kernalmustache
Text: If you have access to a therapist you should book an appointment with them. It's good that you've noticed this early. That means it will be easier to get better. I wish I had some advice for you, but unfortunately I started getting better by focusing on healthy eating and that sounds like something that triggered this for you.
